24/07/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Romanian Economy Ministry announced at the weekend that it plans to shut down 50 mines, most of them located in northern Romania, by the end of this year. According to the ministry's estimations, the costs of the project could reach 125m euros. Since 1997, the government has closed 142 mines and cut jobs in the mining industry from 175,879 to 48,519. This year, 11,000 employees in the sector are expected to be laid off -- 2,500 more than last year. (Bucharest Daily News, Nine o'clock - 24/07/06) 
